# Rosslyn Clinic - AI Website Copy Generator

ğŸ“‹ Project Overview
This repository contains a structured prompt engineering system designed to generate professional, community-focused website copy for Rosslyn Clinic, a public healthcare facility in Rosslyn, Akasia, City of Tshwane, South Africa.
Unlike commercial businesses, public clinics require copy that balances professionalism with accessibility, clarity with compassion, and honesty about service limitations with community trust-building.

ğŸ¥ Business Chosen
Rosslyn Clinic

Type: Public medical clinic
Location: Rosslyn, Akasia â€“ City of Tshwane, South Africa
Target Audience: Local community members seeking affordable, accessible healthcare
Key Challenge: High patient volumes, resource limitations, need for clear communication about services and expectations

ğŸ¯ Problem Being Solved
Public healthcare facilities often struggle with:

âŒ Unclear communication about available services
âŒ Patient confusion about what to expect
âŒ Lack of professional web presence
âŒ Difficulty managing patient expectations around wait times and availability
âŒ Generic or outdated information that doesn't build community trust

This prompt system addresses these issues by generating:

âœ… Clear, honest service descriptions
âœ… Realistic expectation-setting
âœ… Professional yet accessible language
âœ… Community-focused messaging
âœ… Actionable guidance for patients

ğŸ§  Prompt Engineering Strategy
Design Principles

Clarity Over Marketing

Public clinics serve communities, not customers
Prompts avoid sales language and unrealistic promises
Focus on information and guidance

Tone Adaptation

Professional but warm
Respectful of diverse patient backgrounds
Honest about limitations (capacity, stock, wait times)

Structured Modularity

Separate prompts for homepage, services, and CTAs
Reusable across different public healthcare facilities
Easy to adapt for specific clinic needs

Context-Aware

Acknowledges high patient volumes
References local community (Rosslyn, Akasia)
Respects public healthcare realities

