ğŸ“ Prompt Breakdown
1ï¸âƒ£ Homepage Copy Prompt
Purpose: Generate a clear value proposition and set expectations
Key Elements:

Clear headline (clinic's main purpose)
Sub-headline (who it serves + benefit)
Introduction section (services, community focus, patient volume reality)

Tone: Professional, calm, respectful, community-focused
2ï¸âƒ£ Services Page Content Prompt
Purpose: Clearly explain services and reduce patient confusion
Key Elements:

Service names
Patient-friendly explanations
Why patients should use this clinic
Honest note about availability/capacity

Tone: Clear, honest, informative (no jargon or sales language)
3ï¸âƒ£ CTA Sections Prompt
Purpose: Guide patients on next steps without commercial pressure
Key Elements:

Contact/Visit guidance (with early arrival suggestion)
Trust-building (public healthcare values, dignity, respect)
Location-based encouragement (local community focus)

Tone: Supportive, respectful, action-oriented

ğŸ“ How to Use This System
For This Clinic:

Review the prompts in /prompts/
Run them through your chosen AI tool
Review outputs in /outputs/
Customize as needed for specific clinic details

For Other Public Clinics:

Replace clinic name and location
Adjust services list based on facility offerings
Maintain the tone and structure
Keep focus on clarity and community trust

For Other Business Types:
This structure can be adapted by changing:

Tone guidelines (more friendly for salons, more confident for agencies)
Service types
CTA approach (booking vs. visiting)
Value proposition focus

ğŸ’¡ Key Learnings
What Makes This Different from Commercial Copy:

No urgency manipulation â€“ Patients need care, not pressure
Honest about limitations â€“ Builds long-term trust
Community language â€“ "We serve you" vs. "Buy from us"
Educational CTAs â€“ Inform rather than convert

Prompt Engineering Insights:

Specificity in tone prevents generic AI outputs
Structured sections create reusable templates
Context about business type (public vs. private) dramatically changes output quality
Clear instructions about what to avoid is as important as what to include

